1)substr() funtion is used to fetch part of the string
2) It has two syntax
substr(source,pos) pos suggests from where it should starts fetching substring
substr(source,pos,len) len suggests how much length of substring to fetch
3)We can use both positive and negative indexing
Pos starts on left with 1
neg starts on right with -1

select substr('good morning',1) from dual;
SUBSTR('GOOD
------------
good morning
select substr('good morning',5) from dual;
